http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Call-to-strengthen-community-policing/article14026600.ece

Acting chairman, National Human Rights Commission Cyriac Joseph has stressed the need for strong bonds between the police force and the public to ensure human rights.Addressing the valedictory of the national conference on community policing here on Thursday, he said the police had the dual role to ensure the right to a decent life and protect national security and unity. “It is important to maintain human rights while maintaining law and order. Community policing offers a way to balance the two interests”, he said.Shashi Tharoor MP presided. State Police Chief T.P.Senkumar and ADGP B.Sandhya were present.